libhybris: bridge Android-13 system-lib symbols

aurora (Pixel Watch 2) is the first AsteroidOS device running Android-13
system libraries under libhybris. libhybris replaces bionic libc with its
hook table rather than loading it, so libc/runtime symbols imported by the
Android system libs must be present in that table. Several are missing
upstream, leaving them unresolved at load -> asteroid-launcher SIGSEGVs:

  - libc++.so      -> the ARM EHABI unwinder family (_Unwind_*, __aeabi_*)
  - libhidlbase.so -> android_get_device_api_level (libc, API 29+)
  - libselinux.so  -> __system_properties_init (libc property-area init)
  - memfd_create   (libc, API 30+)
  - libbase.so     -> android_fdsan_create_owner_tag (libc, API 29+);
                      crashed Qt's QSGRenderThread when unique_fd wrapped
                      the first gralloc4 dmabuf fd (PC=0 from null GOT
                      slot). Upstream already hooks set_error_level,
                      exchange_owner_tag and close_with_tag, but missed
                      create_owner_tag and the inspection / get_error_level
                      helpers; add them as a disabled no-op consistent with
                      the rest of the family (fdsan's pre-Q behavior).

Map the unwinder + memfd_create straight to the host glibc/libgcc, back
android_get_device_api_level() with ro.build.version.sdk, make
__system_properties_init a success no-op (libhybris serves property reads via
its own __system_property_* hooks), and stub the missing fdsan members so
unique_fd tags every fd with 0 (untagged) and close_with_tag is a plain
close().

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>

--- a/common/hooks.c
+++ b/common/hooks.c
@@ -2893,6 +2893,102 @@
     return close(fd);
 }
 
+// ---- Android-13 system-lib symbol bridges ----
+// Android-13's libc++.so pulls the full ARM EHABI unwinder family and
+// libhidlbase.so pulls libc's android_get_device_api_level(); upstream
+// libhybris bridges none of them, so the hybris linker leaves them
+// unresolved and asteroid-launcher SIGSEGVs at load. The unwind symbols are
+// all exported by the target glibc libgcc_s, so map them straight through.
+// We only take their addresses for the hook table (never call them here), so
+// a void(void) prototype is enough -- the address resolves to the real
+// libgcc_s symbol and is handed to the Android libc++.so, which calls it with
+// the correct ABI.
+extern void _Unwind_Resume(void);
+extern void _Unwind_RaiseException(void);
+extern void _Unwind_DeleteException(void);
+extern void _Unwind_Resume_or_Rethrow(void);
+extern void _Unwind_ForcedUnwind(void);
+extern void _Unwind_Backtrace(void);
+extern void _Unwind_Complete(void);
+extern void _Unwind_GetCFA(void);
+extern void _Unwind_GetRegionStart(void);
+extern void _Unwind_GetLanguageSpecificData(void);
+extern void _Unwind_GetDataRelBase(void);
+extern void _Unwind_GetTextRelBase(void);
+extern void _Unwind_VRS_Get(void);
+extern void _Unwind_VRS_Set(void);
+extern void _Unwind_VRS_Pop(void);
+extern void __gnu_unwind_frame(void);
+extern void __aeabi_unwind_cpp_pr0(void);
+extern void __aeabi_unwind_cpp_pr1(void);
+extern void __aeabi_unwind_cpp_pr2(void);
+
+// libc memfd_create() (API 30+); host glibc provides it.
+extern int memfd_create(const char *name, unsigned int flags);
+
+// libc android_get_device_api_level() (API 29+): return the device SDK level
+// from ro.build.version.sdk (default 29 if the property is unavailable).
+int _hybris_hook_android_get_device_api_level(void)
+{
+    char value[128] = {0};
+    int level;
+    my_property_get("ro.build.version.sdk", value, "29");
+    level = atoi(value);
+    return level > 0 ? level : 29;
+}
+
+// libc __system_properties_init() (plural): bionic maps the property area here.
+// Android-13 libselinux.so (and others) import it. libhybris serves property
+// reads through its own __system_property_* hooks, so the area init is a no-op
+// that just needs to report success.
+int _hybris_hook___system_properties_init(void)
+{
+    return 0;
+}
+
+// libc fdsan family (Android-10+): upstream libhybris already hooks
+// set_error_level, exchange_owner_tag and close_with_tag (just above), but
+// NOT android_fdsan_create_owner_tag -- which Android-13's libbase
+// android::base::unique_fd calls to mint its ownership tag. The symbol is
+// weak in the importing libs, so libbase loads with the GOT slot left NULL;
+// unique_fd then calls it unconditionally and the first fd wrapped (e.g. a
+// gralloc4 dmabuf in Qt's QSGRenderThread) jumps through a NULL pointer ->
+// SIGSEGV (PC=0). Implement create as the disabled no-op tag 0 (untagged),
+// so close_with_tag (already hooked, does close()) and exchange (already
+// hooked, no-op) stay consistent; fd ownership remains correct, only the
+// double-close diagnostic is off -- fdsan's pre-Q behavior. Also stub the
+// inspection helpers and get_error_level (set_error_level is already hooked
+// upstream): A13 libutils/libui/libgui/libbinder all use unique_fd and may
+// call these from log paths.
+uint64_t _hybris_hook_android_fdsan_create_owner_tag(int type, uint64_t tag)
+{
+    (void)type;
+    (void)tag;
+    return 0;
+}
+
+uint64_t _hybris_hook_android_fdsan_get_owner_tag(int fd)
+{
+    (void)fd;
+    return 0;
+}
+
+const char *_hybris_hook_android_fdsan_get_tag_type(uint64_t tag)
+{
+    (void)tag;
+    return "native_handle";
+}
+
+uint64_t _hybris_hook_android_fdsan_get_tag_value(uint64_t tag)
+{
+    return tag;
+}
+
+int _hybris_hook_android_fdsan_get_error_level(void)
+{
+    return 0; /* ANDROID_FDSAN_ERROR_LEVEL_DISABLED */
+}
+
 // old property hooks for pre-android 8 approach
